rogant/know\u2011it\u2011all, relatively weak leadership skills, hot\u2011tempered, described as a loner and moody, no explicit evidence of communication ability.\n- **Fit:** Strong problem\u2011solving and responsibility, but potential deficits in leadership, communication, and crew interaction could be risky on long\u2011haul flights.\n**Preliminary Assessment:**\nCandidate\u202fB currently appears to best meet the core requirements of reliability, technical competence, and calmness under pressure, which are essential for safe long\u2011distance operations. The main reservation is his interpersonal style, which could affect crew harmony.\n**Open Questions / Information Gaps:**\n1. **Candidate\u202fA:** Is there any evidence of actual reliability (e.g., punctuality, record of completing duties) or examples of how he handles criticism in practice?\n2. **Candidate\u202fC:** Do we have any data on his technical competence (e.g., aircraft systems knowledge, navigation skills) beyond decision\u2011making speed?\n3. **Candidate\u202fD:** Can we obtain specific examples of his communication style with crew members (e.g., clarity, tone) and any incidents that illustrate his \u201carrogant\u201d or \u201chot\u2011tempered\u201d behavior?\n4. **Candidate\u202fB:** Are there any documented instances where his uncooperative or pretentious behavior impacted crew performance, and how were they resolved?\nGathering answers to these questions will help confirm whether Candidate\u202fB\u2019s interpersonal drawbacks are manageable or if another candidate might outweigh them.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_1\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We have gathered info from agents 2 and 3. Now need to produce our public contribution: summarize overall evaluation, perhaps ask further questions to fill gaps. We have info on each candidate:\n\nCandidate A:\n- strengths: anticipates dangerous situations, sees complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership