to see complex connections, anticipate dangerous situations (maybe technical). D solves problems extremely well, concentration. C lacks technical info.\n\nReliability: B 100% reliable. D takes responsibility seriously. A unorganized, not open to criticism. C not willing to further education (maybe not reliability). D maybe reliable.\n\nCalm under pressure: B keeps calm in crisis. C handles stress well. D responds adequately. A? Not mentioned.\n\nTeamwork/communication: A leadership but show-off, not open to ideas. B uncooperative, nasty remarks. C creates positive atmosphere, but difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric. D weak leadership, arrogant, know-it-all, moody.\n\nProfessional development: C not willing to further education. Others? Not mentioned.\n\nThus likely best candidate is B? B has reliability, technical competence, calmness, but cooperation issues. D has responsibility, problem solving, but leadership weak, communication issues. C good crew atmosphere but technical unknown and egocentric. A strong anticipation and spatial vision but unorganized and not open to criticism.\n\nWe need to weigh: For long-distance flights, reliability and calmness are critical. B is 100% reliable and calm. Technical competence also strong. Cooperation is a concern but maybe can be mitigated? D also strong but leadership weak and communication issues. I'd lean B as best overall, despite cooperation issues.\n\nWe should state our evaluation, maybe ask others for missing info: e.g., ask about Candidate D's communication skills specifics, or Candidate C's technical competence. Also ask about Candidate A's reliability evidence.\n\nWe can ask targeted questions to fill gaps.\n\nNow produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE: include summary, current assessment, ask questions.\n\nVote: Candidate B.\n\nNow produce METADATA_JSON."}
